ristianity emerges. This insightful work, placing emphasis on the major figures and both the scholarly lines of development and the appropriate lines for future research, will set the debate in a clearer and more and succinct manner. It will serve as a critical point of reference for further discussion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and lawxHistory. 0aChristianity and other religionsxJudaismxHistory. 0aJewish lawxHistory. 0aJudaismxRelationsxChristianityxHistory. 0aReligion and lawxHistory. 0aReligionxRome (Empire). 0aReligion. 0aReligious communitiesxHistoryxRome. 0aReligious communitieszRomexHistory. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh1 aBaumgarten, Albert I., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWassén, Cecilia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWesterholm, Stephen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920632840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206328423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206328/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles